As of 2011, Daylight Saving Time is not used in Russia anymore (see [Time in Russia|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_in_Russia]). That means that in winter time, Jira will be applying incorrect timestamps for Russian time zones. 

This concerns time zones in Russia as well the [FET time zone|http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Further-eastern_European_Time], used in Belarus (and Kaliningrad).

